# Performance & Accessibility (Lighthouse 95+)

## Constraints

- **Measurement First:** Avoid premature optimization. Identify specific bottlenecks via profiling (DevTools Performance tab) before applying any fixes.
- **Performance Budgets:**
    - **Core Web Vitals:** LCP ≤ 2.5s, INP ≤ 200ms, CLS ≤ 0.1.
    - **API & Load:** API response time < 200ms (p95). Time to Interactive (TTI) < 3.5s on 4G connections.
    - **Bundle Size:** Keep initial feature chunks < 50kb. Enforce dynamic imports (`next/dynamic`) for heavy dependencies.
- **LCP Optimization:** Use the `priority` attribute for the first visible `Image` (Next.js) or hero assets to prioritize loading.
- **Image & Data Standards:**
    - Define explicit `width` and `height` to prevent CLS.
    - Use `<picture>` with `source` tags for complex art direction or resolution switching.
    - Prevent N+1 query patterns; strictly use pagination or optimized includes/joins for all data-driven components.
- **Icon & Font Strategy:** Use tree-shakable icons (e.g., `lucide-react`). Apply `swap` display strategy for fonts, optimized via `next/font` or local self-hosting.
- **A11y SSOT:** All interactive elements MUST have `aria-label`, `role`, or an associated `<label>`. Maintain WCAG AA compliance (4.5:1 contrast ratio).
- **Asset Links:** Reference `ui-components.mdc` for specific Skeleton and Layout Shift (CLS) implementation rules.

## Bans

- **Layout Shift:** Forbidden to render content without reserved dimensions (use Skeletons).
- **Native Img:** Forbidden to use raw `<img>` tags.
- **Blocking JS:** Forbidden to use heavy 3rd party scripts in the main thread (use `next/script` or Web Workers).
- **A11y Gaps:** Forbidden to use `div` as a button without `tabIndex` and `onKeyDown`.
- **Alt Text:** Forbidden to leave `alt` attributes empty or generic (e.g., "image").

## Correct Implementation

<example>
// Optimized LCP and A11y
import Image from "next/image";

export const Hero = () => (
  <section>
    <h1>{t("title")}</h1>
    <Image 
      src="/hero.webp" 
      alt="Dashboard analytics overview" 
      width={1200} 
      height={600} 
      priority 
    />
    <button aria-label="Start free trial" onClick={handleAction}>
      {t("cta")}
    </button>
  </section>
);
</example>

## Incorrect Implementation

<incorrect-example>
// BAN: Native img, no dimensions, no priority, no aria-label
const BadHero = () => (
  <div>
    <img src="/hero.png" />
    <div onClick={handleAction}>Click here</div>
  </div>
);
</incorrect-example>
